HEADWORD: Thunderous
<hw>Thun"der*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Written also
<ets>thundrous</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Producing thunder.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How he before the <qex>thunderous</qex> throne doth lie.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Making a noise like thunder; sounding loud and deep;
sonorous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Thun"der*ous*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
